":"Meat topping"},{"content":"Place garlic, onions and tomatoes into mixing bowl and chop <b>30 sec\/speed 5<b>. Transfer mixture into simmering basket, sprinkle with salt and allow to stand for 5 minutes, then squeeze out as much liquid as possible."},{"content":"Place parsley and mint into mixing bowl and chop <b>3 sec\/speed 6<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula."},{"content":"Add reserved strained tomato mixture, cumin, cayenne pepper, cinnamon, paprika, all-spice, chilli flakes, pomegranate molasses and lamb mince and knead <b>3 min\/<b>. Transfer to a bowl and set aside."},{"isHeader":true,"content":"Assembly and baking"},{"content":"Grease a baking tray or baking stone and place it in oven. Preheat oven to 250ºC."},{"content":"Turn reserved dough out onto a floured surface. Using floured hands, quickly knead and divide dough into 6 equal pieces. With a rolling pin roll each ball into a thin flat circle (approx. Ø 18-20 cm) and place on the preheated baking tray."},{"content":"Divide reserved meat topping into 6 equal portions and gently spread evenly and thinly across each piece of dough. Sprinkle each flatbread with a pinch of salt and pine nuts. Bake for 10-15 minutes (250°C) or until the edges of the flatbreads are golden and crispy. Repeat with a second baking tray if necessary."},{"content":"Squeeze a little lemon juice over each flatbread and serve with lemon quarters."}],"hintsAndTricks":["Accompany with salad and a savoury yogurt drink, garnished with fresh chopped mint and parsley leaves."],"basicInfo":["medium","30m","1h 50m","6 pieces"]}